<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?> 
<crossway-bible>
	<book title="Romans" num="44">
		<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009001">
		</marker>
		<chapter num="9">
			<heading
				>
				God's Sovereign Choice
			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="1">
				<crossref let="a" cid="c45009001.1">
				</crossref>
				I am speaking the truth in ChristùI am not lying; my conscience bears me witness in the Holy Spiritù
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009002">
			</marker>
			<verse num="2">
				that I have great sorrow and unceasing anguish in my heart.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009003">
			</marker>
			<verse num="3">
				For 
				<crossref let="b" cid="c45009003.1">
				</crossref>
				I could wish that I myself were 
				<crossref let="c" cid="c45009003.2">
				</crossref>
				accursed and cut off from Christ for the sake of my brothers,
				<note nid="n45009003.1">
				</note>
				 my kinsmen 
				<crossref let="d" cid="c45009003.3">
				</crossref>
				according to the flesh.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009004">
			</marker>
			<verse num="4">
				They are 
				<crossref let="e" cid="c45009004.1">
				</crossref>
				Israelites, and to them belong 
				<crossref let="f" cid="c45009004.2">
				</crossref>
				the adoption, 
				<crossref let="g" cid="c45009004.3">
				</crossref>
				the glory, 
				<crossref let="h" cid="c45009004.4">
				</crossref>
				the covenants, 
				<crossref let="i" cid="c45009004.5">
				</crossref>
				the giving of the law, 
				<crossref let="j" cid="c45009004.6">
				</crossref>
				the worship, and 
				<crossref let="k" cid="c45009004.7">
				</crossref>
				the promises.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009005">
			</marker>
			<verse num="5">
				To them belong 
				<crossref let="l" cid="c45009005.1">
				</crossref>
				the patriarchs, and from their race, according to the flesh, is the Christ 
				<crossref let="m" cid="c45009005.2">
				</crossref>
				who is God over all, 
				<crossref let="n" cid="c45009005.3">
				</crossref>
				blessed forever. Amen.
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009006">
			</marker>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="6">
				But it is not as though the word of God has failed. For not all who are descended from Israel belong to Israel,
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009007">
			</marker>
			<verse num="7">
				and not all are children of Abraham 
				<crossref let="o" cid="c45009007.1">
				</crossref>
				because they are his offspring, but 
				<crossref let="p" cid="c45009007.2">
				</crossref>
				<crossref cid="t45009007.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				Through Isaac shall your offspring be named.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009008">
			</marker>
			<verse num="8">
				This means that it is not the children of the flesh who are the children of God, but 
				<crossref let="q" cid="c45009008.1">
				</crossref>
				the children of the promise are counted as offspring.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009009">
			</marker>
			<verse num="9">
				For this is what the promise said: 
				<crossref let="r" cid="c45009009.1">
				</crossref>
				<crossref cid="t45009009.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				About this time next year I will return, and Sarah shall have a son.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009010">
			</marker>
			<verse num="10">
				And not only so, but 
				<crossref let="s" cid="c45009010.1">
				</crossref>
				also when Rebekah had conceived children by one man, our forefather Isaac,
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009011">
			</marker>
			<verse num="11">
				though they were not yet born and had done nothing either good or badùin order that God's purpose of election might continue, not because of works but because of 
				<crossref let="t" cid="c45009011.1">
				</crossref>
				him who callsù
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009012">
			</marker>
			<verse num="12">
				she was told, 
				<crossref let="u" cid="c45009012.1">
				</crossref>
				<crossref cid="t45009012.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				The older will serve the younger.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009013">
			</marker>
			<verse num="13">
				As it is written, 
				<crossref let="v" cid="c45009013.1">
				</crossref>
				<crossref cid="t45009013.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				Jacob I loved, but Esau I hated.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009014">
			</marker>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="14">
				What shall we say then? 
				<crossref let="w" cid="c45009014.1">
				</crossref>
				Is there injustice on God's part? By no means!
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009015">
			</marker>
			<verse num="15">
				For he says to Moses, 
				<crossref let="x" cid="c45009015.1">
				</crossref>
				<crossref cid="t45009015.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				I will have mercy on whom I have mercy, and I will have compassion on whom I have compassion.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009016">
			</marker>
			<verse num="16">
				So then it depends not on human will or exertion,
				<note nid="n45009016.1">
				</note>
				 but on God, who has mercy.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009017">
			</marker>
			<verse num="17">
				For the Scripture says to Pharaoh, 
				<crossref let="y" cid="c45009017.1">
				</crossref>
				<crossref cid="t45009017.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				For this very purpose I have raised you up, that I might show my power in you, and that my name might be proclaimed in all the earth.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009018">
			</marker>
			<verse num="18">
				So then he has mercy on whomever he wills, and he hardens whomever he wills.
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009019">
			</marker>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="19">
				You will say to me then, 
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				Why does he still find fault? For 
				<crossref let="z" cid="c45009019.1">
				</crossref>
				who can resist his will?
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009020">
			</marker>
			<verse num="20">
				But who are you, O man, 
				<crossref let="a" cid="c45009020.1">
				</crossref>
				to answer back to God? 
				<crossref let="b" cid="c45009020.2">
				</crossref>
				Will what is molded say to its molder, 
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				Why have you made me like this?
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009021">
			</marker>
			<verse num="21">
				<crossref let="c" cid="c45009021.1">
				</crossref>
				Has the potter no right over the clay, to make out of the same lump 
				<crossref let="d" cid="c45009021.2">
				</crossref>
				one vessel for honorable use and another for dishonorable use?
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009022">
			</marker>
			<verse num="22">
				What if God, desiring to show his wrath and to make known his power, has endured with much patience 
				<crossref let="e" cid="c45009022.1">
				</crossref>
				vessels of wrath 
				<crossref let="f" cid="c45009022.2">
				</crossref>
				prepared for destruction,
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009023">
			</marker>
			<verse num="23">
				in order to make known 
				<crossref let="g" cid="c45009023.1">
				</crossref>
				the riches of his glory for vessels of mercy, which he 
				<crossref let="h" cid="c45009023.2">
				</crossref>
				has prepared beforehand for gloryù
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009024">
			</marker>
			<verse num="24">
				even us whom he 
				<crossref let="i" cid="c45009024.1">
				</crossref>
				has called, 
				<crossref let="j" cid="c45009024.2">
				</crossref>
				not from the Jews only but also from the Gentiles?
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009025">
			</marker>
			<verse num="25">
				As indeed he says in Hosea,

				<end-paragraph
					>
				</end-paragraph>
				<begin-block-indent
					>
				</begin-block-indent>
				<begin-paragraph class="line-group">
				</begin-paragraph>
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="k" cid="c45009025.1">
				</crossref>
				<crossref cid="t45009025.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				Those who were not my people I will call 
				<q class="begin-single" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				my people,
				<q class="end-single" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				and her who was not beloved I will call 
				<q class="begin-single" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				beloved.
				<q class="end-single" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009026">
			</marker>
			<verse num="26">
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="l" cid="c45009026.1">
				</crossref>
				<crossref cid="t45009026.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				And in the very place where it was said to them, 
				<q class="begin-single" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				You are not my people,
				<q class="end-single" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				there they will be called 
				<crossref let="m" cid="c45009026.2">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-single" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				sons of the living God.
				<q class="end-single" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				<end-line
					>
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<end-block-indent
				>
			</end-block-indent>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009027">
			</marker>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="27">
				And Isaiah cries out concerning Israel: 
				<crossref let="n" cid="c45009027.1">
				</crossref>
				<crossref cid="t45009027.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				Though the number of the sons of Israel
				<note nid="n45009027.1">
				</note>
				 be as the sand of the sea, 
				<crossref let="o" cid="c45009027.2">
				</crossref>
				only a remnant of them will be saved,
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009028">
			</marker>
			<verse num="28">
				for the Lord will carry out his sentence upon the earth fully and without delay.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009029">
			</marker>
			<verse num="29">
				And as Isaiah predicted,

				<end-paragraph
					>
				</end-paragraph>
				<begin-block-indent
					>
				</begin-block-indent>
				<begin-paragraph class="line-group">
				</begin-paragraph>
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				<crossrefs
					>
					<crossref let="p" cid="c45009029.1">
					</crossref>
					<crossref let="q" cid="c45009029.2">
					</crossref>
				</crossrefs>
				<crossref cid="t45009029.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				If the Lord of hosts had not left us offspring,
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="r" cid="c45009029.3">
				</crossref>
				we would have been like Sodom
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				and become like Gomorrah.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				<end-line
					>
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<end-block-indent
				>
			</end-block-indent>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009030">
			</marker>
			<heading
				>
				Israel's Unbelief
			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="30">
				What shall we say, then? 
				<crossref let="s" cid="c45009030.1">
				</crossref>
				That Gentiles who did not pursue righteousness have attained it, that is, 
				<crossref let="t" cid="c45009030.2">
				</crossref>
				a righteousness that is by faith;
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009031">
			</marker>
			<verse num="31">
				but that Israel 
				<crossref let="u" cid="c45009031.1">
				</crossref>
				who pursued a law that would lead to righteousness
				<note nid="n45009031.1">
				</note>
				<crossref let="v" cid="c45009031.2">
				</crossref>
				did not succeed in reaching that law.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009032">
			</marker>
			<verse num="32">
				Why? Because they did not pursue it by faith, but as if it were based on works. They have stumbled over the 
				<crossref let="w" cid="c45009032.1">
				</crossref>
				stumbling stone,
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v45009033">
			</marker>
			<verse num="33">
				as it is written,

				<end-paragraph
					>
				</end-paragraph>
				<begin-block-indent
					>
				</begin-block-indent>
				<begin-paragraph class="line-group">
				</begin-paragraph>
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="x" cid="c45009033.1">
				</crossref>
				<crossref cid="t45009033.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				Behold, I am laying in Zion 
				<crossref let="y" cid="c45009033.2">
				</crossref>
				a stone of stumbling, and a rock of offense;
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="z" cid="c45009033.3">
				</crossref>
				and whoever believes in him will not be 
				<crossref let="a" cid="c45009033.4">
				</crossref>
				put to shame.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				<end-line
					>
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<end-block-indent
				>
			</end-block-indent>
		</chapter>
	</book>
</crossway-bible>


